On Feb 9, 2006, at 2:39 PM, LarryEdson(-at-)comcast.net wrote:
> I use a small pair of vice grips to pinch the line when I pull the 
> engine. Its not good for the long term health of the hose but it sure 
> beats having gas pour on me while I fumble with stuffing something in 
> the end to cork it.

I only use the vicegrips-pinching-the-hose trick long enough to stuff 
something into the end to cork it with.  "Something" usually winds up 
being a suitably sized bolt with the hoseclamp tightened around it for 
insurance .. and so I don't lose the clamp.
